HEADWORD: Peasant
<hw>Peas"ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>pa⟦ium⟧sant</ets> (the <it>i</it> being perh. due to confusion with
the p. pr. of verbs), <ets>pa⟦ium⟧san</ets>, F. <ets>paysan</ets>, fr.
OF. & F. <ets>pays</ets> country, fr. L. <ets>pagus</ets> the country.
See <er>Pagan</er>.]</ety> <def>A countryman; a rustic; especially, one
of the lowest class of tillers of the soil in European
countries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Countryman; rustic; swain; hind.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

